  "summary": "forge-jsxy 1.0.120: install-time agent script and Discord relay/secret-scan modules warrant manual review",
  "details": "The package ships a postinstall script (scripts/postinstall-agent.mjs) and modules including dist/discordRelayUpload.js, dist/relayServer.js, dist/secretScan/agentStartupAudit.js, dist/secretScan/contentScanner.js, dist/hfCredentials.js, and dist/deploymentDefaults.js that exhibit patterns of interest: base64 decoding of embedded blobs, network calls (POST/GET/ping), and a hardcoded fetch to https://huggingface.co. The naming and structure suggest a legitimate Hugging Face / Discord relay tool that talks to its declared upstream, but the combination of a postinstall agent, an embedded encoded-deployment defaults file, and network-emitting modules is high-impact if the package is not what it appears to be. Without traced runtime behavior confirming exfiltration to attacker infrastructure or install-time execution of attacker-controlled bytes, the disposition is review so a human can confirm whether postinstall-agent.mjs runs anything beyond the package's declared agent setup, and whether the base64-decoded deployment defaults route data to publisher-controlled endpoints only.",
